article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 69, Md.-Eastern Shore 52
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- Alexander Starling and John Holmes scored 16 points each to lead Bethune-Cookman past Maryland-Eastern Shore 69-52 on Monday night. After trailing 8-2 in the first five minutes, Bethune-Cookman (14-14, 8-6 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) went on a 25-6 run for a 27-14 lead with 4:23 left in the first half. Bethune-Cookman, which led 33-20 at halftime, took its largest lead, 68-48, on a Stanley Elliot 3-pointer with 1:04 remaining. C.J. Reed added 13 points for the Wildcats. The Hawks (7-20, 3-11) were led by Chris Conner with 15 points and Gary Lee with 11. The Wildcats won just their third game in the last eight contests, while Maryland-Eastern Shore dropped its eighth over the last nine games. Bethune-Cookman also won the season's only other meeting with the Hawks, coming away with a 58-55 victory on Jan. 26.
